casebody.data:
LOUIS SILVERSTEIN, Plaintiff and Appellant, v. PAMELA L. VULTE, Defendant and Respondent.

Before Sedgwick and Van Vorst, JJ.

Decided March 14, 1879. 31. Practice. 1. Resettling findings of law. (a) Order denying motion for, affirmed. The case was tried before one of the judges of this court, who delivered an opinion and made and filed his findings of fact and law. Plaintiff, claiming that the findings of law were not in accordance with the facts found and the opinion, moved before another judge for a re-settlement, which motion was denied. *591Christopher Fine, of counsel, for appellant. Albert Mathews, of counsel, for respondent. Per Curiam.

Order affirmed, with $10 costs and disbursements.
